================================================================================
mcp-gnu-units — BOOTSTRAP TODO
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GOAL: from this empty directory, stand up the skeleton of a pure-Python MCP
server that will (later) expose the GNU `units` engine — precise unit conversion,
dimensional analysis, and unit-expression evaluation over the 3000+ unit GNU
units database. When every box below is checked the server starts over stdio,
exposes exactly ONE tool, and that tool reports the server's availability +
version information. No domain features yet (conversion/dimensional-analysis
come later — see the FUTURE note at the end).

DONE = `mcp-gnu-units` runs, a client lists one tool, and calling it returns
       {status: "available", name, version, ...}.

Checkbox legend:  [ ] not started   [~] in progress   [x] done

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHY THIS PROJECT / POSITIONING  (from the 2026-06-19 Glama landscape research)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Glama unit-conversion field is crowded with category-locked converters
(zazencodes' "Unit Converter MCP" with 15 one-per-category tools is the leader;
guptaprakhariitr, kdaehun00, CSOAI, Robbo-lab follow). The literal slug
`unit-converter-mcp` collides across THREE authors, and NO server uses the GNU
`units` engine. Open keyword space nobody owns: "GNU units", "dimensional
analysis", "unit expression", "SI base units". We win on capabilities every
existing server lacks: arbitrary unit-EXPRESSION evaluation and DATABASE
search/definition lookup.

  NAME      : mcp-gnu-units   (matches the mcp-* family: mcp-tmux/-bytesmith/
              -kodi/-abacus/-molecules; owns the uncontested "GNU units" keyword
              + still substring-matches "units"; PyPI/GitHub free as of
              2026-06-19.)
              ⚠️ WHY NOT mcp-units: that name is ALREADY TAKEN on PyPI
              (pypi.org/project/mcp-units, v0.3.3, "MCP server for cooking unit
              conversions", author sellisd) — a competing converter — so `uvx
              mcp-units` was impossible. Verified free alternates on file:
              gnu-units-mcp, mcp-unitsmith, mcp-unit-convert, mcp-dimension.
              LESSON: check PyPI + Glama for the dist name BEFORE committing to
              it — the name is effectively frozen once published/indexed.
  LICENSE   : GPL-3.0-or-later. NOTE: the GNU units database (definitions.units)
              is itself GPL-3.0-or-later, © Free Software Foundation — reusing it
              in a GPLv3 server is squarely compatible. Keep its header intact.
================================================================================


